						<div class="postbody">See my 6502 stacks treatise at <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://wilsonminesco.com/stacks/">http://wilsonminesco.com/stacks/</a><!-- m -->, especially chapters 4, 5, and 6.  Chapter 6 is titled &quot;Parameter-passing methods.&quot;<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Unfortunately, the ZP way doesn't allow for recursion</div><br />Actually, it does, although you'll use X for the pointer.  The method is also shown in the stacks treatise above, being introduced in chapter 4, &quot;Virtual stacks and various ways to implement them.&quot;</div>

					
